{
  "id": "RAW_81efbff8",
  "title": "认识 EverOS：一个开源、Markdown 优先的智能体记忆运行时，具备混合 BM25 + 向量检索与自我进化技能",
  "url": "https://www.marktechpost.com/2026/06/29/meet-everos-an-open-source-markdown-first-agent-memory-runtime-with-hybrid-bm25-vector-retrieval-and-self-evolving-skills/",
  "date": "2026-06-29 18:42:50",
  "author": "Asif Razzaq",
  "siteName": "MarkTechPost",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">EverMind has released <strong><a href=\"https://github.com/EverMind-AI/EverOS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">EverOS</a></strong>, an open-source memory runtime for AI agents. It ships under an Apache 2.0 license. It targets a problem agent builders hit early: large language models are stateless. The conversation ends, and the context is gone.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">EverOS proposes a different substrate. Instead of locking memory inside a vector database, it writes memory as plain Markdown files. Those files become the source of truth that agents read, edit, and search across sessions.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-tl-dr\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>TL;DR</strong></h2>\n  <ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n   <li>EverOS stores agent memory as editable Markdown, indexed by SQLite and LanceDB.</li>\n   <li>Hybrid retrieval blends BM25, vector search, and scalar filtering in one query.</li>\n   <li>Cases distill into reusable Skills, giving agents procedural, self-evolving memory.</li>\n   <li>Benchmark scores are strong but EverMind-reported; verify on your own workload.</li>\n   <li>It is open source under Apache 2.0, with cloud and self-hosted parity.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h2 id=\"h-what-is-everos\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>What is EverOS?</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">EverOS is a Python library and a local-first memory runtime. It runs as a server with a CLI and a FastAPI HTTP API, async-first throughout. You drop it into an existing agent loop rather than rebuilding your stack.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The design separates two memory tracks. User-side memory holds Profiles, Episodes, Facts, and Foresights. Agent-side memory holds Cases and Skills. Keeping them separate is unusual; most libraries center on chat history alone.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Every record lands as a <code>.md</code> file. You can open, edit, grep, and Git-version it, or view it in Obsidian. EverAlgo, a separate stateless library, handles the extraction algorithms. EverOS orchestrates and persists the results.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The endpoint stack is OpenAI-protocol compatible. It connects to OpenAI, OpenRouter, vLLM, Ollama, or DeepInfra by changing a base URL. That keeps integration close to a single configuration change.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The runtime is local-first by default. Data never has to leave your environment, and every layer is inspectable. A managed EverOS Cloud option exists for teams that prefer not to self-host. Both share the same SDK, retrieval engine, and memory format.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-the-architecture-markdown-sqlite-and-lancedb\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>The Architecture — Markdown, SQLite, and LanceDB</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">EverOS uses a three-piece storage stack. Markdown is the source of truth. SQLite manages state and queues. LanceDB manages vectors, BM25, and scalar filters.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This is deliberately lighter than a typical production memory setup. There is no required MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Milvus, Redis, or Kafka. For solo developers and small teams, that lowers operational cost.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Retrieval is hybrid. A single LanceDB query combines BM25 keyword matching, dense vector search, and scalar filtering. EverMind markets this multimodal retrieval path as mRAG.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A cascade index sync keeps files and indexes aligned. Editing a <code>.md</code> file triggers a file-watcher that re-syncs the index. Memory stays inspectable without going stale.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Retrieval is also orthogonal across identifiers. You can scope a search by <code>user_id</code>, <code>agent_id</code>, <code>app_id</code>, <code>project_id</code>, and <code>session_id</code>. That scoping is important in multi-agent and multi-user deployments where data isolation is required.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-how-memory-self-evolves-cases-become-skills\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How Memory Self-Evolves — Cases Become Skills</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A distinctive feature is procedural memory. EverOS records each completed agent task as a Case. Repeated successful patterns are distilled offline into reusable Skills.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This is the ‘self-evolving’ claim, stated plainly. Skills are shared across an agent team, with no manual curation and no hardcoding. The goal is agents that improve with use instead of restarting each session.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Version 1.1.0 added more lifecycle machinery. It introduced Knowledge APIs for source-backed Markdown pages with taxonomy and topic search. It also added Reflection, an offline process that merges episode clusters and refines profiles and skills between sessions.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The memory model is simple. Episodic memory answers ‘what happened.’ Profile memory answers ‘who is this user.’ Procedural memory answers ‘how is this task done.’</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-benchmark\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Benchmark</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">EverMind team reports 93.05% on LoCoMo, 83.00% on LongMemEval, and 93.04% on HaluMem. It also cites sub-500ms p95 retrieval latency. LoCoMo and LongMemEval measure long-term conversational memory; HaluMem targets memory hallucination. These numbers come from EverMind posts.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>The table below compares EverOS against common alternatives on concrete design dimensions:</strong></p>\n  <figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\">\n   <table class=\"has-fixed-layout\">\n    <thead>\n     <tr>\n      <th>Dimension</th>\n      <th>EverOS</th>\n      <th>Naive RAG</th>\n      <th>Full context window</th>\n      <th>Other memory libraries</th>\n     </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Source of truth</td>\n      <td>Plain Markdown <code>.md</code> files</td>\n      <td>Vector DB records</td>\n      <td>Prompt only</td>\n      <td>API or database state</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Local stack</td>\n      <td>Markdown + SQLite + LanceDB</td>\n      <td>Vector DB + app code</td>\n      <td>None</td>\n      <td>Often managed services</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Retrieval</td>\n      <td>Hybrid BM25 + vector + scalar</td>\n      <td>Dense vector only</td>\n      <td>None (no retrieval)</td>\n      <td>Varies</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Procedural memory</td>\n      <td>Cases distilled into Skills</td>\n      <td>None</td>\n      <td>None</td>\n      <td>Rare</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Multimodal ingest</td>\n      <td>PDF, image, Office, URL in one call</td>\n      <td>Manual pipeline</td>\n      <td>Via context only</td>\n      <td>Partial</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>LoCoMo accuracy</td>\n      <td>93.05% (EverMind-reported)</td>\n      <td>—</td>\n      <td>N/A (context limit)</td>\n      <td>Varies</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>License</td>\n      <td>Apache 2.0</td>\n      <td>Varies</td>\n      <td>N/A</td>\n      <td>Varies / proprietary</td>\n     </tr>\n    </tbody>\n   </table>\n  </figure>\n  <h2 id=\"h-use-cases-with-real-examples\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Use Cases, With Real Examples</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The library links to working integrations. They show what persistent memory enables in real products.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Hive Orchestrator is a browser-native hive-mind for CLI coding agents. Claude Code, Codex, Gemini, and OpenCode collaborate as real PTY processes through a shared team protocol.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Reunite uses semantic memory for public-value search. Parents describe what they remember, children describe what they recall, and the system surfaces connections.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Other examples span healthcare and hardware. They include an Alzheimer’s memory assistant and an AI wearable. The wearable listens to everyday life and converts it into memory. A study buddy with self-evolving memory is also among the examples. The wider ecosystem adds a Claude Code plugin and an MCP-based memory layer for coding assistants.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-a-five-minute-code-walkthrough\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>A Five-Minute Code Walkthrough</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Installation uses standard Python tooling. EverOS requires Python 3.12 or newer. The local demo needs no API keys.</p>\n  <div class=\"dm-code-snippet dark dm-normal-version default no-background-mobile\" snippet-height=\"\" style=\"background-color:#abb8c3\">\n   <div class=\"control-language\">\n    <div class=\"dm-buttons\">\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-left\"></div>\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-right\">\n      <a id=\"dm-copy-raw-code\"><span class=\"dm-copy-text\">Copy Code</span></a>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <pre class=\" no-line-numbers\"><code id=\"dm-code-raw\" class=\" no-wrap language-php\"># Requires Python 3.12+\nuv pip install everos        # or: pip install everos\neveros demo                  # local educational visualizer, no keys\neveros init                  # paste OpenRouter + DeepInfra keys into .env\neveros server start          # starts the FastAPI server\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:8000/health   # -&gt; {\"status\":\"ok\"}</code></pre>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Adding and searching memory are plain HTTP calls. The example below stores a fact, forces extraction, then retrieves it.</p>\n  <div class=\"dm-code-snippet dark dm-normal-version default no-background-mobile\" snippet-height=\"\" style=\"background-color:#abb8c3\">\n   <div class=\"control-language\">\n    <div class=\"dm-buttons\">\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-left\"></div>\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-right\">\n      <a id=\"dm-copy-raw-code\"><span class=\"dm-copy-text\">Copy Code</span></a>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <pre class=\" no-line-numbers\"><code id=\"dm-code-raw\" class=\" no-wrap language-php\"># 1) Add a short conversation\ncurl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/memory/add \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"session_id\":\"demo-001\",\"app_id\":\"default\",\"project_id\":\"default\",\n       \"messages\":[{\"sender_id\":\"alice\",\"role\":\"user\",\"timestamp\":1750000000000,\n                    \"content\":\"I love climbing in Yosemite every spring.\"}]}'\n\n# 2) Flush to force extraction (local demo)\ncurl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/memory/flush \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"session_id\":\"demo-001\",\"app_id\":\"default\",\"project_id\":\"default\"}'\n\n# 3) Search it back\ncurl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/memory/search \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"user_id\":\"alice\",\"app_id\":\"default\",\"project_id\":\"default\",\n       \"query\":\"Where do I like to climb?\",\"top_k\":5}'</code></pre>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Multimodal ingestion is an optional extra. Installing <code>everos[multimodal]</code> adds parsing for images, PDFs, and audio. Office documents additionally require LibreOffice, which converts files to PDF before parsing.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-try-it-interactive-memory-demo\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Try It: Interactive Memory Demo</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The embedded demo below simulates the EverOS loop in your browser. Add a snippet, watch it get extracted and tagged, then search it back through hybrid retrieval. It is illustrative and does not connect to a live server.</p>\n  <!-- ===== EverOS Interactive Demo - paste into a WordPress \"Custom HTML\" block ===== -->\n  <div id=\"everos-demo-wrap\" style=\"max-width:920px;margin:0 auto;\">\n   <iframe class=\"lazyload\" id=\"everos-demo-frame\" title=\"EverOS Memory Lifecycle Interactive Demo\" loading=\"lazy\" srcdoc=\"&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;\n&lt;title&gt;EverOS Memory Lifecycle — Interactive Simulator&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;style&gt;\n  :root{\n    --bg:#ffffff;\n    --panel:#f6f8fa;\n    --panel-2:#eef1f4;\n    --ink:#1c2128;\n    --muted:#5b6573;\n    --line:#e2e6ea;\n    --accent:#76B900;\n    --accent-ink:#3d6300;\n    --episodic:#2f6fed;\n    --profile:#8a4fe0;\n    --skill:#d9821a;\n    --episodic-bg:#eaf1fe;\n    --profile-bg:#f2ecfd;\n    --skill-bg:#fdf2e3;\n    --good:#1a9c52;\n    --shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(16,24,40,.06),0 1px 3px rgba(16,24,40,.1);\n  }\n  *{box-sizing:border-box}\n  body{\n    margin:0;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;\n    background:var(--bg);color:var(--ink);line-height:1.5;\n    -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;\n  }\n  .wrap{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:20px 18px 8px}\n  .mono{font-family:'JetBrains Mono','SF Mono',ui-monospace,Menlo,Consolas,monospace}\n  .head{text-align:left;margin-bottom:14px}\n  .badge{display:inline-block;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent-ink);background:rgba(118,185,0,.12);border:1px solid rgba(118,185,0,.3);padding:3px 9px;border-radius:999px}\n  h1{font-size:22px;margin:10px 0 4px;letter-spacing:-.01em}\n  .sub{color:var(--muted);font-size:14px;max-width:640px}\n  .tabs{display:flex;gap:6px;margin:18px 0 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}\n  .tab{appearance:none;border:0;background:none;cursor:pointer;font:inherit;font-weight:600;font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);padding:9px 12px;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;margin-bottom:-1px}\n  .tab.active{color:var(--ink);border-bottom-color:var(--accent)}\n  .tab .n{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:18px;height:18px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--panel-2);font-size:11px;margin-right:6px;color:var(--muted)}\n  .tab.active .n{background:var(--accent);color:#fff}\n  .view{display:none;animation:fade .25s ease}\n  .view.active{display:block}\n  @keyframes fade{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(4px)}to{opacity:1;transform:none}}\n  .card{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:16px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}\n  .label{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:8px}\n  .chips{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:7px;margin-bottom:12px}\n  .chip{cursor:pointer;font-size:12.5px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;padding:7px 10px;color:var(--ink);transition:.12s}\n  .chip:hover{border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent-ink)}\n  textarea,input[type=text]{width:100%;font:inherit;font-size:14px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:9px;padding:11px 12px;color:var(--ink);resize:vertical}\n  textarea:focus,input:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--accent);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(118,185,0,.15)}\n  .row{display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:11px}\n  .btn{appearance:none;border:0;cursor:pointer;font:inherit;font-weight:600;font-size:14px;background:var(--accent);color:#fff;padding:10px 16px;border-radius:9px;transition:.12s}\n  .btn:hover{background:#69a700}\n  .btn:disabled{opacity:.5;cursor:not-allowed}\n  .btn.ghost{background:#fff;color:var(--ink);border:1px solid var(--line)}\n  .btn.ghost:hover{border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent-ink);background:#fff}\n  .pipe{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:6px;margin:16px 0 6px}\n  .stage{text-align:center;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--muted);padding:9px 4px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;background:#fff;transition:.2s}\n  .stage.on{color:#fff;background:var(--accent);border-color:var(--accent);transform:translateY(-2px)}\n  .stage.done{color:var(--accent-ink);background:rgba(118,185,0,.1);border-color:rgba(118,185,0,.4)}\n  .stage small{display:block;font-weight:500;font-size:9px;opacity:.8;margin-top:2px}\n  .mdcard{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-left-width:4px;border-radius:9px;padding:13px 14px;margin-top:10px;animation:fade .3s ease}\n  .mdcard.episodic{border-left-color:var(--episodic)}\n  .mdcard.profile{border-left-color:var(--profile)}\n  .mdcard.skill{border-left-color:var(--skill)}\n  .mtag{display:inline-block;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px}\n  .mtag.episodic{color:var(--episodic);background:var(--episodic-bg)}\n  .mtag.profile{color:var(--profile);background:var(--profile-bg)}\n  .mtag.skill{color:var(--skill);background:var(--skill-bg)}\n  .fm{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin:8px 0 6px;white-space:pre-wrap;line-height:1.6}\n  .fm .k{color:var(--accent-ink)}\n  .mtext{font-size:14px;color:var(--ink)}\n  .tagline{margin-top:8px;display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap}\n  .kw{font-size:11px;background:var(--panel-2);border-radius:6px;padding:2px 7px;color:var(--muted)}\n  .empty{color:var(--muted);font-size:13.5px;text-align:center;padding:26px 10px}\n  .count{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-left:auto}\n  .result{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:9px;padding:13px 14px;margin-top:10px;animation:fade .3s ease}\n  .result .top{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:7px}\n  .scorebar{height:6px;background:var(--panel-2);border-radius:4px;overflow:hidden;margin:7px 0 3px}\n  .scorebar i{display:block;height:100%;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--accent),#9ed64a);border-radius:4px;transition:width .5s ease}\n  .scoremeta{display:flex;gap:14px;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--muted)}\n  .scoremeta b{color:var(--ink);font-weight:600}\n  .src{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:7px;border-top:1px dashed var(--line);padding-top:7px}\n  .latency{font-size:12px;color:var(--good);font-weight:600}\n  .hint{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px}\n  .note{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);background:var(--panel-2);border-radius:8px;padding:9px 11px;margin-top:14px}\n  .foot{text-align:center;font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);padding:16px 0 8px;border-top:1px solid var(--line);margin-top:18px}\n  .foot b{color:var(--accent-ink);font-weight:700}\n  @media (max-width:560px){.pipe{grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr)}.stage{font-size:10px}.stage small{display:none}h1{font-size:19px}}\n&lt;/style&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;wrap&quot; id=&quot;app&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;div class=&quot;head&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;span class=&quot;badge&quot;&gt;Interactive · EverOS Memory Lifecycle&lt;/span&gt;\n    &lt;h1&gt;From a stateless message to retrievable memory&lt;/h1&gt;\n    &lt;p class=&quot;sub&quot;&gt;Add a snippet, watch EverOS extract and tag it, store it as Markdown, then search it back through hybrid retrieval. This is an illustrative simulation of the EverOS loop — it runs locally in your browser and is not connected to a live server.&lt;/p&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n  &lt;div class=&quot;tabs&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;button class=&quot;tab active&quot; data-tab=&quot;add&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;Add memory&lt;/button&gt;\n    &lt;button class=&quot;tab&quot; data-tab=&quot;store&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;Memory store&lt;/button&gt;\n    &lt;button class=&quot;tab&quot; data-tab=&quot;search&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;Search&lt;/button&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n  &lt;!-- ADD --&gt;\n  &lt;section class=&quot;view active&quot; id=&quot;view-add&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Pick a conversation snippet, or write your own&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;chips&quot; id=&quot;seedChips&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;textarea id=&quot;memInput&quot; rows=&quot;2&quot; placeholder=&quot;e.g. I love climbing in Yosemite every spring.&quot;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;pipe&quot; id=&quot;pipe&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;stage&quot; data-s=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Ingest&lt;small&gt;add()&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;stage&quot; data-s=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Extract&lt;small&gt;EverAlgo&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;stage&quot; data-s=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Tag&lt;small&gt;type&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;stage&quot; data-s=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Markdown&lt;small&gt;.md write&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;stage&quot; data-s=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Index&lt;small&gt;SQLite+LanceDB&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;button class=&quot;btn&quot; id=&quot;addBtn&quot;&gt;Add to EverOS&lt;/button&gt;\n        &lt;button class=&quot;btn ghost&quot; id=&quot;seedAllBtn&quot;&gt;Seed 4 examples&lt;/button&gt;\n        &lt;span class=&quot;count&quot; id=&quot;addCount&quot;&gt;0 memories stored&lt;/span&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div id=&quot;lastCard&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;note&quot;&gt;EverOS auto-extracts and tags each memory as &lt;b&gt;Profile&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Episodic&lt;/b&gt;, or &lt;b&gt;Skill&lt;/b&gt; — no manual curation. The same record is written as a plain &lt;span class=&quot;mono&quot;&gt;.md&lt;/span&gt; file (the source of truth) and indexed for retrieval.&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/section&gt;\n\n  &lt;!-- STORE --&gt;\n  &lt;section class=&quot;view&quot; id=&quot;view-store&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:0&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot; style=&quot;margin:0&quot;&gt;Markdown source of truth&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;span class=&quot;count&quot; id=&quot;storeCount&quot;&gt;0 memories&lt;/span&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div id=&quot;storeList&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/section&gt;\n\n  &lt;!-- SEARCH --&gt;\n  &lt;section class=&quot;view&quot; id=&quot;view-search&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;label&quot;&gt;Ask a question — retrieval runs over your stored memories&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;chips&quot; id=&quot;queryChips&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;queryInput&quot; placeholder=&quot;e.g. Where do I like to climb?&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;button class=&quot;btn&quot; id=&quot;searchBtn&quot;&gt;Search memory&lt;/button&gt;\n        &lt;span class=&quot;latency&quot; id=&quot;latency&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div id=&quot;results&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;hint&quot;&gt;Hybrid retrieval combines a &lt;b&gt;BM25&lt;/b&gt; keyword score and a &lt;b&gt;vector&lt;/b&gt; semantic score, then ranks. Scores below are illustrative and computed in-browser.&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/section&gt;\n\n  &lt;div class=&quot;foot&quot;&gt;Interactive explainer built for &lt;b&gt;Marktechpost&lt;/b&gt; · EverOS is open source under Apache 2.0&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;script&gt;\n(function(){\n  var memories = [];\n  var idc = 1;\n\n  var seeds = [\n    &quot;I love climbing in Yosemite every spring.&quot;,\n    &quot;My favorite coffee shop is Blue Bottle in SOMA.&quot;,\n    &quot;To deploy: run make build, then make release on the staging branch.&quot;,\n    &quot;The Q3 product launch slipped to October because of the security audit.&quot;\n  ];\n  var queries = [\n    &quot;Where do I like to climb?&quot;,\n    &quot;What coffee do I prefer?&quot;,\n    &quot;How do I ship a release?&quot;,\n    &quot;Why was the launch delayed?&quot;\n  ];\n\n  // simple concept map for the &quot;semantic&quot; score (illustrative)\n  var concepts = {\n    climb:[&quot;climb&quot;,&quot;climbing&quot;,&quot;yosemite&quot;,&quot;mountain&quot;,&quot;hiking&quot;,&quot;spring&quot;,&quot;outdoor&quot;,&quot;bouldering&quot;],\n    coffee:[&quot;coffee&quot;,&quot;cafe&quot;,&quot;blue&quot;,&quot;bottle&quot;,&quot;soma&quot;,&quot;espresso&quot;,&quot;latte&quot;,&quot;drink&quot;,&quot;shop&quot;],\n    deploy:[&quot;deploy&quot;,&quot;ship&quot;,&quot;release&quot;,&quot;build&quot;,&quot;staging&quot;,&quot;make&quot;,&quot;branch&quot;,&quot;pipeline&quot;,&quot;push&quot;],\n    launch:[&quot;launch&quot;,&quot;q3&quot;,&quot;october&quot;,&quot;audit&quot;,&quot;slip&quot;,&quot;delay&quot;,&quot;delayed&quot;,&quot;security&quot;,&quot;schedule&quot;]\n  };\n\n  function tokens(s){return (s.toLowerCase().match(/[a-z0-9]+/g)||[]);}\n  var stop = {&quot;i&quot;:1,&quot;a&quot;:1,&quot;the&quot;:1,&quot;to&quot;:1,&quot;my&quot;:1,&quot;do&quot;:1,&quot;is&quot;:1,&quot;in&quot;:1,&quot;on&quot;:1,&quot;of&quot;:1,&quot;it&quot;:1,&quot;me&quot;:1,&quot;so&quot;:1,&quot;was&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:1,&quot;where&quot;:1,&quot;how&quot;:1,&quot;what&quot;:1,&quot;like&quot;:1,&quot;then&quot;:1};\n\n  function classify(text){\n    var t = text.toLowerCase();\n    if(/\\b(deploy|run |install|build|configure|steps?|release|make |how to|command)\\b/.test(t)) return &quot;skill&quot;;\n    if(/\\b(i love|i like|favorite|favourite|i prefer|i am|i'm|my name|i work|i live)\\b/.test(t)) return &quot;profile&quot;;\n    return &quot;episodic&quot;;\n  }\n  function keywords(text){\n    var seen={},out=[];\n    tokens(text).forEach(function(w){if(w.length&gt;2&amp;&amp;!stop[w]&amp;&amp;!seen[w]){seen[w]=1;out.push(w);}});\n    return out.slice(0,5);\n  }\n  function typeNote(type){\n    if(type===&quot;skill&quot;) return &quot;procedural memory — a reusable how-to the agent can replay&quot;;\n    if(type===&quot;profile&quot;) return &quot;long-term identity / preference, kept across sessions&quot;;\n    return &quot;episodic memory — a specific event the agent can recall later&quot;;\n  }\n\n  // ---- pipeline animation ----\n  var stages = document.querySelectorAll('#pipe .stage');\n  function runPipeline(cb){\n    stages.forEach(function(s){s.classList.remove('on','done');});\n    var i=0;\n    (function step(){\n      if(i&gt;0) stages[i-1].classList.add('done');\n      if(i&lt;stages.length){\n        stages[i].classList.add('on');\n        i++;\n        setTimeout(step,260);\n      } else {\n        stages.forEach(function(s){s.classList.remove('on');s.classList.add('done');});\n        setTimeout(cb,160);\n      }\n    })();\n  }\n\n  function ts(){\n    var d=new Date();\n    return d.toISOString().slice(0,19).replace('T',' ');\n  }\n\n  function mdMarkup(m){\n    return '&lt;div class=&quot;mdcard '+m.type+'&quot;&gt;'+\n      '&lt;span class=&quot;mtag '+m.type+'&quot;&gt;'+m.type.toUpperCase()+'&lt;/span&gt;'+\n      '&lt;div class=&quot;fm mono&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;type:&lt;/span&gt; '+m.type+'  '+\n      '&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;user_id:&lt;/span&gt; alice  &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;app_id:&lt;/span&gt; default\\n'+\n      '&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;project_id:&lt;/span&gt; default  &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;session_id:&lt;/span&gt; '+m.session+'  &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;ts:&lt;/span&gt; '+m.ts+'&lt;/div&gt;'+\n      '&lt;div class=&quot;mtext&quot;&gt;'+escapeHtml(m.text)+'&lt;/div&gt;'+\n      '&lt;div class=&quot;tagline&quot;&gt;'+m.keywords.map(function(k){return '&lt;span class=&quot;kw&quot;&gt;#'+k+'&lt;/span&gt;';}).join('')+'&lt;/div&gt;'+\n      '&lt;/div&gt;';\n  }\n  function escapeHtml(s){return s.replace(/&amp;/g,'&amp;amp;').replace(/&lt;/g,'&amp;lt;').replace(/&gt;/g,'&amp;gt;');}\n\n  function addMemory(text){\n    var type = classify(text);\n    var m = {id:idc++, text:text.trim(), type:type, keywords:keywords(text), session:&quot;demo-00&quot;+((idc%4)+1), ts:ts()};\n    memories.push(m);\n    return m;\n  }\n\n  function refreshCounts(){\n    document.getElementById('addCount').textContent = memories.length+(memories.length===1?' memory stored':' memories stored');\n    document.getElementById('storeCount').textContent = memories.length+(memories.length===1?' memory':' memories');\n  }\n\n  function renderStore(){\n    var el=document.getElementById('storeList');\n    if(!memories.length){el.innerHTML='&lt;div class=&quot;empty&quot;&gt;No memories yet. Add one on the first tab.&lt;/div&gt;';return;}\n    el.innerHTML = memories.slice().reverse().map(mdMarkup).join('');\n  }\n\n  // ---- search ----\n  function conceptScore(qTok, mTok){\n    // semantic: do query and memory share a concept bucket?\n    var best=0;\n    for(var c in concepts){\n      var qHit=qTok.some(function(t){return concepts[c].indexOf(t)&gt;-1;});\n      var mHit=mTok.some(function(t){return concepts[c].indexOf(t)&gt;-1;});\n      if(qHit&amp;&amp;mHit) best=Math.max(best,1);\n    }\n    return best;\n  }\n  function bm25ish(qTok,mTok){\n    var set={}; mTok.forEach(function(t){set[t]=(set[t]||0)+1;});\n    var hits=0,uniq=0,seen={};\n    qTok.forEach(function(t){\n      if(stop[t])return;\n      if(set[t]){hits+=set[t]; if(!seen[t]){uniq++;seen[t]=1;}}\n    });\n    var qLen=qTok.filter(function(t){return !stop[t];}).length||1;\n    return Math.min(1, (uniq/qLen)*0.7 + Math.min(hits,3)/3*0.3);\n  }\n\n  function search(query){\n    var qTok=tokens(query);\n    var scored=memories.map(function(m){\n      var mTok=tokens(m.text);\n      var bm=bm25ish(qTok,mTok);\n      var vec=conceptScore(qTok,mTok)*(0.55+Math.min(bm,0.45));\n      var hybrid=0.5*bm+0.5*vec;\n      return {m:m,bm:bm,vec:vec,hybrid:hybrid};\n    }).filter(function(r){return r.hybrid&gt;0.04;})\n      .sort(function(a,b){return b.hybrid-a.hybrid;})\n      .slice(0,3);\n    return scored;\n  }\n\n  function renderResults(query){\n    var el=document.getElementById('results');\n    var lat=document.getElementById('latency');\n    if(!memories.length){el.innerHTML='&lt;div class=&quot;empty&quot;&gt;No memories stored yet — add a few first.&lt;/div&gt;';lat.textContent='';return;}\n    var res=search(query);\n    var ms=Math.floor(80+Math.random()*360); // &lt;500ms p95, illustrative\n    lat.textContent='retrieved in '+ms+' ms (p95 &lt; 500ms)';\n    if(!res.length){el.innerHTML='&lt;div class=&quot;empty&quot;&gt;No memory matched that query. Try one of the suggested questions.&lt;/div&gt;';return;}\n    el.innerHTML = res.map(function(r,i){\n      var pct=Math.round(r.hybrid*100);\n      return '&lt;div class=&quot;result&quot;&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div class=&quot;top&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mtag '+r.m.type+'&quot;&gt;'+r.m.type.toUpperCase()+'&lt;/span&gt;'+\n        '&lt;b style=&quot;font-size:13px&quot;&gt;Match #'+(i+1)+'&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div class=&quot;mtext&quot;&gt;'+escapeHtml(r.m.text)+'&lt;/div&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div class=&quot;scorebar&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;width:'+pct+'%&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div class=&quot;scoremeta&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hybrid &lt;b&gt;'+r.hybrid.toFixed(2)+'&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;'+\n        '&lt;span&gt;bm25 &lt;b&gt;'+r.bm.toFixed(2)+'&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;'+\n        '&lt;span&gt;vector &lt;b&gt;'+r.vec.toFixed(2)+'&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div class=&quot;src&quot;&gt;source: &lt;span class=&quot;mono&quot;&gt;~/.everos/episodes/'+r.m.session+'/'+r.m.id+'.md&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;'+\n        '&lt;/div&gt;';\n    }).join('');\n  }\n\n  // ---- wire up ----\n  function show(card){ document.getElementById('lastCard').innerHTML=mdMarkup(card); }\n\n  document.getElementById('addBtn').addEventListener('click',function(){\n    var v=document.getElementById('memInput').value.trim();\n    if(!v) return;\n    var btn=this; btn.disabled=true;\n    runPipeline(function(){\n      var m=addMemory(v);\n      show(m); refreshCounts(); renderStore();\n      document.getElementById('memInput').value='';\n      btn.disabled=false;\n    });\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById('seedAllBtn').addEventListener('click',function(){\n    var btn=this; btn.disabled=true;\n    seeds.forEach(function(s){ if(!memories.some(function(m){return m.text===s;})) addMemory(s); });\n    refreshCounts(); renderStore();\n    runPipeline(function(){ show(memories[memories.length-1]); btn.disabled=false; });\n  });\n\n  document.getElementById('searchBtn').addEventListener('click',function(){\n    var q=document.getElementById('queryInput').value.trim();\n    if(!q) return; renderResults(q);\n  });\n  document.getElementById('queryInput').addEventListener('keydown',function(e){if(e.key==='Enter')document.getElementById('searchBtn').click();});\n\n  // chips\n  var sc=document.getElementById('seedChips');\n  seeds.forEach(function(s){var c=document.createElement('span');c.className='chip';c.textContent=s;c.onclick=function(){document.getElementById('memInput').value=s;};sc.appendChild(c);});\n  var qc=document.getElementById('queryChips');\n  queries.forEach(function(s){var c=document.createElement('span');c.className='chip';c.textContent=s;c.onclick=function(){document.getElementById('queryInput').value=s;document.getElementById('searchBtn').click();};qc.appendChild(c);});\n\n  // tabs\n  document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(function(t){\n    t.addEventListener('click',function(){\n      document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(function(x){x.classList.remove('active');});\n      document.querySelectorAll('.view').forEach(function(x){x.classList.remove('active');});\n      t.classList.add('active');\n      document.getElementById('view-'+t.dataset.tab).classList.add('active');\n      if(t.dataset.tab==='store') renderStore();\n      reportHeight();\n    });\n  });\n\n  renderStore(); refreshCounts();\n\n  // auto-resize for WordPress iframe embedding (component height + buffer)\n  function reportHeight(){\n    var h=document.getElementById('app').offsetHeight+40;\n    if(window.parent){ window.parent.postMessage({everosDemoHeight:h},'*'); }\n  }\n  window.addEventListener('load',reportHeight);\n  window.addEventListener('resize',reportHeight);\n  var obs=new MutationObserver(reportHeight);\n  obs.observe(document.getElementById('app'),{childList:true,subtree:true});\n})();\n&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\"></iframe>\n  </div>\n  <!-- ===== end EverOS demo ===== -->\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n  <hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\">\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Check out the&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://github.com/EverMind-AI/EverOS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Repo</a> </strong>and<strong> <a href=\"https://evermind.ai/everos\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Technical details</a></strong>.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Also,&nbsp;feel free to follow us on&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://x.com/intent/follow?screen_name=marktechpost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><mark>Twitter</mark></a></strong>&nbsp;and don’t forget to join our&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/machinelearningnews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">150k+ML SubReddit</a></strong>&nbsp;and Subscribe to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.aidevsignals.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">our Newsletter</a></strong>. Wait! are you on telegram?&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://t.me/machinelearningresearchnews\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">now you can join us on telegram as well.</a></strong></p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Need to partner with us for promoting your GitHub Repo OR Hugging Face Page OR Product Release OR Webinar etc.?&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://forms.gle/wbash1wF6efRj8G58\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><mark>Connect with us</mark></a></strong></p>\n  <!-- MOLONGUI AUTHORSHIP PLUGIN 5.2.9 -->\n  <!-- https://www.molongui.com/wordpress-plugin-post-authors -->\n  <!-- CONTENT END 2 -->\n  <div class=\"td-a-rec td-a-rec-id-content_bottom  tdi_77 td_block_template_1\">\n   <div id=\"bsad-700x300\">\n    <div class=\"bs-stage\">\n     <div class=\"bs-scale\">\n      <a class=\"bs-ad\" href=\"https://pxllnk.co/cuv4rk8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"BigSet on GitHub — describe your ideal dataset in plain English, and BigSet builds it\"> \n       <div class=\"wrap\">\n        <div class=\"left\">\n         <div class=\"kicker\">\n          <span class=\"brand\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>tinyfish.ai</span><span class=\"pill\">Open Source</span>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"name\">\n          Big<b>Set</b>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"tag\">Describe your ideal dataset in plain English, and BigSet builds it.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"right\">\n         <div class=\"cta\">\n          <span>Explore on GitHub</span><span class=\"arrow\">→</span>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div> \n      </a>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "EverOS 是一个开源、Markdown 优先的智能体记忆运行时，具备混合 BM25 + 向量检索与自我进化技能，专为持久化的 AI 智能体状态而设计。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "EverOS 是一个开源、Markdown 优先的智能体记忆运行时，具备混合 BM25 + 向量检索与自我进化技能，专为持久化的 AI 智能体状态而设计。",
  "summary": "EverMind 发布了 EverOS，一个基于 Apache 2.0 协议的开源 AI 智能体记忆运行时。它通过将智能体记忆存储为纯 Markdown 文件，并由 SQLite 和 LanceDB 索引，解决了 LLM 的无状态特性。该架构支持混合检索，在单个查询中结合了 BM25 关键词匹配、稠密向量搜索和标量过滤。其一个显著特性是程序性记忆：完成的智能体任务被记录为案例，重复出现的成功模式会在离线状态下被提炼为可复用的技能，从而实现无需人工干预的自我进化。该运行时以本地优先、异步优先为原则，并包含一个 FastAPI 服务器、CLI 以及兼容 OpenAI 协议的端点。EverMind 团队报告其在 LoCoMo 和 LongMemEval 上的基准测试得分分别为 93.05% 和 83.00%，但这些为自行报告的数据。集成示例包括多智能体编码、用于搜索的语义记忆以及健康助手。该项目是开源的，面向寻求可检查、持久化智能体记忆的独立开发者和小型团队。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "EverOS 将智能体记忆存储为纯 Markdown 文件，而非向量数据库。",
      "explanation": "这种设计使记忆具有人类可读、可编辑和版本可控的特性，降低了小型团队的运维开销。"
    },
    {
      "point": "检索是混合式的：在单个 LanceDB 查询中结合了 BM25、稠密向量和标量过滤。",
      "explanation": "mRAG 路径结合了关键词和语义搜索，相比纯向量系统提高了召回率。"
    },
    {
      "point": "程序性记忆通过案例和技能实现自我进化。",
      "explanation": "重复出现的成功任务模式会被提炼为可复用的技能，智能体可以在不同会话中应用这些技能，无需人工干预。"
    },
    {
      "point": "该架构是本地优先的，并在 Apache 2.0 协议下开源。",
      "explanation": "数据可以保留在用户环境中，其技术栈（Markdown + SQLite + LanceDB）避免了繁重的基础设施依赖。"
